Tere Bin Episode 25 - [Eng Sub] - Yumna Zaidi - Wahaj Ali - Digitally Presented by Nisa BB Cream - 22nd March 2023 - HAR PAL GEO

Tere Bin Digitally presented by Nisa BB Cream

Meerab is an ambitious and beautiful young girl who wants to pursue higher studies. Her entire world revolves around her parents and she believes in them the most. Her strong and confident personality makes her stand against social injustices around her.

On the contrary, Murtasim hails from a powerful and influential family. He respects and values the morals and traditions of his family and refuses to let the family down.

Meerab‚Äôs life takes an unexpected turn when she finds out about her family‚Äôs decision regarding her and Murtasim‚Äôs life. Meerab‚Äôs hatred towards Murtasim continues to grow as a family secret from the past resurfaces. Coming from different backgrounds and mindsets, Murtasim begins to realize Meerab‚Äôs arrogant behaviour towards him and begins to consider her a challenge for himself. On the other hand, Meerab who is used to living her life on her own terms refuses to accept Murtasim‚Äôs family traditions and unnecessary social barriers.

Soon their lives go through a series of emotional sufferings and misunderstandings where it becomes difficult for them to coexist. Despite their hatred towards each other, will Meerab and Murtasim accept their true feelings or will the dynamics of ego and self-respect force them to stay apart?

snippet.title: BIG ICE CREAM | Biggest Stick ice making | Watermelon ice | Kiwi ice | Milk ice | Fruit ice Making
snippet.description:
In our childhood, we enjoy those moments with tasting stick ice. We call this ice "Kuchi ice". Today in our village, we made the three most giant colorful stick ice with fruits and milk. We made three types of ice cream. The first one is milk. The second is watermelon. The third one is Kiwi.

Childhood memory comes again! Tasty!

Tere Bin Episode 26 Teaser - 22nd March 2023 - HAR PAL GEO

Meerab is an ambitious and beautiful young girl who wants to pursue higher studies. Her entire world revolves around her parents and she believes in them the most. Her strong and confident personality makes her stand against social injustices around her.

On the contrary, Murtasim hails from a powerful and influential family. He respects and values the morals and traditions of his family and refuses to let the family down.

Meerab‚Äôs life takes an unexpected turn when she finds out about her family‚Äôs decision regarding her and Murtasim‚Äôs life. Meerab‚Äôs hatred towards Murtasim continues to grow as a family secret from the past resurfaces. Coming from different backgrounds and mindsets, Murtasim begins to realize Meerab‚Äôs arrogant behaviour towards him and begins to consider her a challenge for himself. On the other hand, Meerab who is used to living her life on her own terms refuses to accept Murtasim‚Äôs family traditions and unnecessary social barriers.

Soon their lives go through a series of emotional sufferings and misunderstandings where it becomes difficult for them to coexist. Despite their hatred towards each other, will Meerab and Murtasim accept their true feelings or will the dynamics of ego and self-respect force them to stay apart?

Today we are going to see how to make less oily and perfect puri. Puri is generally made on festive days like Gudhi padwa, dasara etc. Today we will make such that will absorb less oil. Yes, here are a few tips to make crispy and fluffy puri that absorbs minimum oil. I will give you few tips and tricks during the video. Puri is a popular puffed Indian bread. It is prepared form wheat flour and deep fried. It is mostly enjoyed on festival days with different Indian desserts. The puries should be fluffy and soft. You can try this recipe at home and drop a comment for me. Do not forget to like, share and subscribe.

Ingredients:
‚Ä¢ 2 cups Wheat flour
‚Ä¢ Salt to taste
‚Ä¢ Water 
‚Ä¢ Oil for frying

Method:
‚Ä¢ Mix wheat flour and salt well and add a little water at a time to knead stiff dough. 
‚Ä¢ Cover and rest the dough for at least 15-20 minutes. 
‚Ä¢ Knead the dough well once more until it becomes smooth and even. 
‚Ä¢ You can make small dough balls and roll puris from it. 
‚Ä¢ Or divide the dough into 2 parts and make one of them smooth and even. It has to be 
  smooth. 
‚Ä¢ Keep the left over dough always covered. 
‚Ä¢ Roll out a big chapatti from the dough. The chapatti should be even.  
‚Ä¢ Avoid use of oil or dry flour while rolling the puri. 
‚Ä¢ Make puris with the help of a katori or a lid. 
‚Ä¢ Heat up oil on medium heat. 
‚Ä¢ While dropping puri in hot oil make sure the smooth side should face downwards and the 
  rolled side should be upper side.
‚Ä¢ Drop puri in hot oil and fry well on medium to high heat. 
‚Ä¢ Press a little and when lower side is fried well flip the puri over and fry well from other side 
  too. 
‚Ä¢ When puri is fried well from other side too, take it out, drain excess oil and transfer it into 
  dish. Puri is all ready.
Tips:
‚Ä¢ Avoid use of water while kneading the dough. Do not use hot or cold water when you knead 
  dough. 
‚Ä¢ Always knead stiff dough. 
‚Ä¢ Never make puris immediately after kneading dough. Rest the dough for at least 15-20 
  minutes. 
‚Ä¢ Avoid use of oil or dry flour while rolling the puri. 
‚Ä¢ Make sure you fry each side of puri once. Avoid flipping puri many times.

*About* 
------------

               Yeh kahani hai ek sanyukt parivaar mai rehnewale Modi khaandaan ki. Izzatdaar, ameer aur naamcheen hone ke bawajud, ghar ke sanskaar aur sanskriti hain inka saccha dhan. Iss ghar ko chalati hai choti bahu, Kokilaben jissey darte hain saare sadasya. Kokilaben ke bade bete, Ahem ki shaadi hojati hai Gopi se joh hai ek saaf dil ki siddhi saadhi, anpapdh ladki. Unke jethani ke bete, Jigar ki shaadi hojati hai Gopi ki behen, Raashi se joh hai bohot hi chaalaak aur nakhrel. 
              Raashi hamesha dikhati hai neecha Gopi ko aur karti hai uske liye mushkilen taiyaar. Par Gopi ka haath thama Kokilaben ne aur banaya ussey hoshiyaar. Iss saas-bahu ki jodi ne apne pyaar, dulaar aur balidaan se bandhe rakha hai Modi parivaar ko.

snippet.title: Iddat | A Short Film | Muskan Sharma | Parinda Films
snippet.description:
"Iddat" is a movie about a girl who elopes and marries a boy from a different caste. Her husband's actions lead to her life being shattered. Will her family forgive her and accept her back into their lives? The movie explores themes of love, forgiveness, and acceptance in the face of difficult circumstances.

snippet.title: NEW! Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah - Ep 3725 - 22 Mar 2023 - Teaser
snippet.description:
Episode 3725: Manoranjan Ka Khazana
--------------------------------------------------------
Asit Kumarr Modi Ji talks about Gokuldham and how it has inspired him to make this creative project, which includes nursery rhymes and digital games. He introduces the games, which are inspired by Gokuldham people like Jethalal and Bhide and his scooter "Sakharam". He promises huge fun and entertainment from these digital projects. Tapu Sena talks about everyone's involvement in developing the apps, like Goli's music, Gogi's graphics, and Pinku's coding. Tapu also gets praised for his leadership skills. Asit Kumarr Modi Ji also talks about launching this project in all regional languages soon because Gokuldham is a melting pot of cultures.

Show Name ‚Äì Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah
Star Cast ‚Äì  Dilip Joshi, Disha Vakani, Amit Bhatt, Nitish Bhaluni
Episodes No - 3725, 22 Mar 2023
Produced By - Asit Kumar Modi

#TaarakMehtaKaOoltahChashmah #‡§§‡§æ‡§∞‡§ï‡§Æ‡•á‡§π‡§§‡§æ‡§ï‡§æ‡§â‡§≤‡•ç‡§ü‡§æ‡§ö‡§∂‡•ç‡§Æ‡§æ #sab 

Click here to subscribe to SAB TV:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC6-F5tO8uklgE9Zy8IvbdFw?sub_confirmation=1

Click here to subscribe to SonyLIV: 
http://www.sonyliv.com/signin

About The Show
----------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in Gokuldham Co-operative Society and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. Jethalal lives in Gokuldham society and owns an electronics shop.  'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Nitish Bhaluni). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises.

Click here to watch the episode of Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah :
https://www.sonyliv.com/dplnk?schema=sony://asset/1000214412

snippet.title: NEW! Ep 3724 - Asit Bhai & Tapu Sena Have A Special Announcement! | Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah
snippet.description:
Click here to Subscribe to Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah Official Channel: https://www.youtube.com/taarakmehtakaooltahchashmah?sub_confirmation=1 

Click here to watch all your favorite Episode videos: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gqFEadNxmd8&list=PLPbh-P_C0BzRYOkpGxKL-6QmvYSL_ZuCu 

We bring to you the best videos from your favorite show Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah. So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.

About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in "Gokuldham Co-operative Society" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Shailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi / Raj Anadkat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalal.

Cast:
---------
Dilip Joshi as Jethalal Champaklal Gada
Disha Vakani as Daya Jethalal Gada
Raj Anadkat / Bhavya Gandhi as Tipendra Jethalal Gada (Tapu) 
Amit Bhatt as Champaklal Jayantilal Gada
Shailesh Lodha as Taarak Mehta
Sunayana Fozdar / Neha Mehta as Anjali Taarak Mehta
Tanuj Mahashabde as Krishnan Subramaniam Iyer
Munmun Dutta as Babita Krishnan Iyer
Mandar Chandwadkar as Aatmaram Tukaram Bhide
Sonalika Joshi as Madhvi Aatmaram Bhide
Nidhi Bhanushali / Palak Sidhwani as Sonalika Aatmaram Bhide (Sonu) 
Gurucharan Singh/ Balwinder suri as Roshan Singh Harjeet Singh Sodhi
Jennifer Mistry Bansiwal as Roshan Kaur Roshan Singh Sodhi
Kavi Kumar Azad / Nirmal Soni as Dr. Hansraj Hathi 
Ambika Ranjankar as Komal Hansraj Hathi
Kush Shah as Gulabkumar Hansraj Hathi (Goli)
Shyam Pathak as Popatlal Pandey
Sharad Sankla as Abdul
Azhar Shaikh as Pinku

snippet.description:
Episode 3724: Suspense Khatam Hua
--------------------------------------------------------
Tapu Sena visits the famous producer and director Mr. Asit Kumar Modi and pitches their creative ideas. Tapu Sena tells Mr. Asit Kumar Modi that during the lockdown period, each one of them learned some extracurricular activity. Goli has developed some skills in music, whereas Sonu nurtured her writing and Tapu in digital mobile gaming. He decides to help Tapu Sena by amalgamating everyone's skills to create something creative. Watch the episode to know what Tapu Sena's project was for which they had created such suspense.
